article.headline: Temple 71, St. Bonaventure 47
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Mardy Collins scored 17 points and grabbed 12 rebounds and Mark Tyndale also had 17 points to lead Temple to a 71-47 win over St. Bonaventure on Wednesday night. Tyndale started the rout early for the Owls, sinking his first three 3-point attempts for a 20-7 lead. Tyndale has only been an 18 percent (12-for-66) 3-pointer shooter this year, but everything worked against the woeful Bonnies. Wayne Marshall scored 13 points for the Owls (7-7, 3-0 Atlantic 10). Temple leads the series 44-6 and beat the Bonnies (1-14, 0-4) for the 24th straight time at home. Wade Dunston scored 17 points and Ahmad Smith added 12 for St. Bonaventure, off to its worst start in school history. The Bonnies, still stung by a March 2003 eligibility scandal that led to NCAA sanctions, have lost 26 of their last 28. The Bonnies tried creeping back into the game after the slow start, once cutting the lead to nine, then again to 10 midway through the second half, only to be pushed back each time by 3-pointers from Dustin Salisbery. They were Salisbery's only points of the game and helped Temple to a 37-22 halftime lead. Temple only shot 39 percent, but was smart with the ball (just six turnovers) and had a 50-31 rebounding advantage. Snowy conditions snarled traffic throughout Philadelphia, getting the Bonnies to the arena only about 15 minutes before the scheduled 7 p.m. start time, which pushed the game back a half-hour.
